dbt <subcommand> [args...]

Generic dbt dispatcher.

If `rlm-dbt-<subcommand>` exists as a function or alias, delegate to
it (passing any remaining args through). Example: `dbt run` opens
the rlm-dbt-run fzf picker; `dbt run -s tag:foo` forwards `-s
tag:foo` to rlm-dbt-run.

Otherwise, invoke plain dbt via _rlm-dbt-bin (respects
DBT_USE_FUSION). Examples: `dbt parse`, `dbt deps`, `dbt debug`,
`dbt source freshness`.

For the plain-dbt path, rlm-dbt auto-injects:
  --project-dir <root>   nearest dbt_project.yml walking up from
                         $PWD (skipped if --project-dir is already
                         in args)
  --profiles-dir <dir>   $DBT_PROFILES_DIR if set (skipped if
                         --profiles-dir is already in args)
  --defer --state <dir>  $DBT_STATE_DIR (via _rlm-dbt-state-info,
                         hard-fails when missing or > 7 days old) —
                         only for subcommands that accept these
                         flags: build, clone, compile, ls, parse,
                         retry, run, seed, show, snapshot, source,
                         test (skipped if --defer / --no-defer /
                         --state already in args)

Existing wrappers (which dbt <subcmd> delegates to): run, build,
test, ls, sandbox.

Examples:
  dbt run                  # delegates to rlm-dbt-run (fzf picker)
  dbt run -s tag:finance   # delegates to rlm-dbt-run with args
  dbt compile -s my_model  # plain dbt compile, --defer/--state auto-injected
  dbt parse                # plain dbt parse, --project-dir auto-injected
  dbt deps                 # plain dbt deps (no defer — not defer-aware)
